             def my_abstract_property(self):
                 ...

     This defines a read-only property; you can also define a
     read-write abstract property using the 'long' form of property
     declaration:

         class C:
             __metaclass__ = ABCMeta
             def getx(self): ...
             def setx(self, value): ...
             x = abstractproperty(getx, setx)



